# ============================================================
#  Quant Desk -- monorepo .gitignore
#  Keep secrets, credentials, heavy/regenerable, and legacy
#  reference code OUT of version control.
# ============================================================

# --- Python venv (rebuild with first_install/install.sh) ---
.venv/
*.egg-info/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# --- Claude Code local state + credentials -- NEVER commit ---
.claude/

# --- Secrets / credentials ---
# config.json holds live broker keys (Fyers etc.); the *.example.json
# templates are safe and intentionally NOT ignored.
**/config.json
**/cert.pem
**/key.pem

# --- Local per-machine user prefs ---
**/preferences.json

# --- Data store (huge + regenerable; >100MB GitHub limit anyway) ---
**/candles.db
**/candles.db-wal
**/candles.db-shm

# --- Logs (may contain auth headers) ---
*.log

# --- Legacy reference codebase: EXCLUDED.
#     Contains plaintext live Upstox credentials. Stays local only. ---
Project1 - Original/

# --- OS cruft ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
